    "history" -> {"12", "14.0", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "coherent state", "Fock space", "Grassmann algebra", 
      "photonic quantum computing"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "CoherentState[<|c1 -> z1, c2 -> z2, ...|>] represents a normalized \
coherent state of Boson or Fermion operators c1, c2, ... belonging to the \
eigenvalues z1, z2, ... of the corresponding operators. CoherentState[c1 -> \
z1, c2 -> z2, ...] gives CoherentState[<|c1 -> z1, c2 -> z2, ...|>] to \
facilitate specifying a coherent state manually. CoherentState[..., {c1, c2, \
...} -> z, ...] gives CoherentState[..., c1 -> z, c2 -> z, ...]. \
CoherentState[..., {c1, c2, ...} -> {z1, z2, ...}, ...] gives \
CoherentState[<|..., c1 -> z1, c2 -> z2, ..., ...|>]. CoherentState[<|...|>, \
<|...|>] returns the Hermitian inner product (not a coherent state) between \
two coherent states specified by the two associations.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "CoherentState", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
    "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "CoherentState", "type" -> 
    "Symbol", "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/CoherentState"}},
